    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sr-Spider Polypeptide-1 is a single chain recombinant spider protein, produced by fermentation in  E. coli.  The starting gene is a synthetically derived copy of the gene from  Araneus diadematus  which codes for Fibroin-4. The protein contains a maximum of 410 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
